column2: Used GL tank rain gauge until 9/30/15, CSS after that
Compared GL tank gauge and tower gauges during analysis - Grass tower bad whole time, CSS gauge shows very good agreement w/ tank
Compared record of tank water level with watering record during analysis - pretty poor agreement - used manual records from Scot
Agreement with water tanks is bad in January 2016
But it's also clear water tank data sets have badly degraded by this point - just one tank is working and there's huge noise
But this date seems safe - the actual rain fell over a ~4 day period and storm wasn't huge - seems unlikely that would have opened midway through storm

column19: Open date is just a guess
